    "Maintenance_Fluids": {
      "text": "Insensible losses = 300-400 cc/m2/d\nAdult Standard: D5 0.45%NS at 75-125 mL/hr + 20meq/L of KCl\nDeficit:Â % dehydration x baseline weight\nDaily volume needed = maintenance + deficit - fluid already given (i.e. boluses)\nHourly rate  daily volume/24 hr\n(or correct 1/2 of deficit in first 8 hr, remainder in next 16)",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": []
    },
    "Electrolytes": {
      "text": "Maintenance Na = 3 mEq/kg/d; K = 2 mEq/kg/d\nDeficit = [desired - measured mEq/L] x fD x wt (kg)\nfD (distribution factor) Na = 0.6, K = 0.6, Cl = 0.2-0.3, HCO3 = 0.5\n(Maintenance + deficit)/daily volume = concentration of electrolyte in fluid to be given\n4mL/kg of H2O lost, ups Na by 1meq",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": []
